    @Public
public interface IOReadableWritable
    This interface must be implemented by every class whose objects have to be serialized to their binary representation and vice-versa. In particular, records have to implement this interface in order to specify how their data can be transferred to a binary representation.

    When implementing this Interface make sure that the implementing class has a default (zero-argument) constructor!
